@page "/gpu"

@* GPU Canvas Demo
   Demonstrates SKGLView with EnableRenderLoop for continuous animation,
   SKRuntimeEffect.BuildShader() for compiling SkSL shaders, and
   touch interaction via uniforms. The entire visual is rendered in SkSL —
   no C# draw calls. C# only handles touch input and passes uniforms. *@

<h1>GPU Canvas</h1>

<p>Pure SkSL lava lamp — all rendering in the shader. Tap or drag to add a blob.</p>

<div class="canvas-container border rounded p-2">

    <SKGLView OnPaintSurface="OnPaintSurface" IgnorePixelScaling="true"
              EnableRenderLoop="true" EnableTouchEvents="true" Touch="OnTouch" />

    <div class="overlay-stats">
        @($"{displayFps:F2}") fps
    </div>

</div>
